cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.NE

This paper discusses the use of robots in complex environments and the challenges of adapting their morphology to better fit the task at hand. This topic falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the theory of Embodied Cognition, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The challenges of designing a robust hardware platform for repeated experiments and self-adaptive morphology are related to systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms for robotics, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
